For more tutorials, visit http://acamso.com

CREATE MACRO

1. Type or paste list of text
2. Click record icon in toolbar
3. Hit Ctrl+H
4. Enter "^" in "Find what" field
5. Enter "＜li＞" in "Replace with" field
6. Click "Regular expression"
7. Click "Replace All"
8. Enter "$" in "Find what" field
9. Enter "＜/li＞" in "Replace with" field
10. Click "Replace All"
11. Hit Ctrl+Home
12. Hit "Enter" key
13. Hit "Up" key
14. Type "＜ol＞"
15. Hit Ctrl+End
16. Hit "Enter" key
17. Type "＜/ol＞"
18. Click stop record icon in toolbar
19. Click Macro ＞＞ Save Current Recorded Macro...
20. Enter a name
21. Click "OK"

RUN MACRO
1. Type or paste list of text
2. Click Macro ＞＞ *name of macro*

Download Notepad++: http://bit.ly/notepad-ac